reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So Much Better than Plastic!
reviews.reviewText: This is a great quality broom. As funny as I felt ordering a broom online, it was well worth it as there is nothing but plastic or flimsy aluminum junk in stores near me. With 4 kids and 3 dogs our brooms have a tendency to get broken SO fast and I just can't stand throwing away all those plastic handles! I was searching for something more environmentally friendly and came across this. To my pleasant surprise it is very sturdy and has already out-lived all of our old plastic brooms, made it through a move into a new house and shows no signs of stress.It sweeps nicely and the handle is very comfortable and smooth with no rough parts in the wood. A couple of other features I like are that the handle is standard size for a dustpan to snap onto and that there is a sturdy fabric loop at the top of the handle to hang it up for storage.*Update after another year-This broom is STILL functional. Granted, the broom head is in need of a deep clean but that's to be expected with the amount of work this thing does. I use this multiple times daily (most of our house is hard floors) and the only actual damage it has sustained is the top fabric loop being broken off by kids, which was due to carelessness, not a quality issue at all. This broom is awesome!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Ordered in spite of the mixed reviews. It’s perfect for my hardwood floors and tile in my home. I don’t know if some people are expecting it to do miracle work of it being a vacuum and that’s why it has negative reviews or I think that people were being way too critical of the broom itself honestly. It’s a perfectly fine broom. It gets the job done. And I can leave it out because it’s aesthetically pleasing. No you can’t sweep your carpet with it. But you can sweep your hard floors with it as good as you can with a broom that you pick up from Walmart or target. The only thing that I would say about it is a dust pan will scratch the wooden handle so do not put a dust pan attachment onto the broom handle because it will scratch it. I just simply hang up my dustpan next to my broom and it makes it so much easier to grab anyways. Honestly that’s worth a trade off of having an ugly broom sitting around for me personally. I enjoy having aesthetically pleasing things out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Kinda fell apart
reviews.reviewText: Well the broom came with this little grey silicon piece that was warped and didn't fit in it's groove. So I removed that, since it's not really necessary. And then the handle came off. I used liquid nails on the bamboo stem and attached it back, now it works like a charm. So, with a little bit of work, you can make this beautiful broom work for you. If you want something that works straight out of the box, buy something else. Oh and something else, it says it's got plastic free packaging, but came wrapped in a full four feet a plastic wrapping. I realize that's probably on Amazon, not this seller, but it was pretty ironic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this pretty broom!
reviews.reviewText: Wood is sturdy and straight, yet light in weight. Sweeping bristles are sturdy, yet soft and bend nicely to effortlessly get into the tile grout crevices. Very nice broom. Very happy. Thanks for the good, protective packaging, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Second time ordering and yet again, the head detached.
reviews.reviewText: I first ordered this broom and it arrived broken, I ordered a replacement. I got the replacement and swept my house once. Put the broom away. Got the broom out to sweep my stairs and the head falls off. I don’t know what I’m missing. It doesn’t connect back on, looks like the screws continuously strip in the plastic that’s somehow supposed to hold the most vital part of the broom together. It’s been an incredibly inconvenient purchase for me. I wouldn’t bother. I liked their other products but this one has failed me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best broom EVER!!
reviews.reviewText: This cute broom not only looks clean and sleek, it preforms like a super hero!! It get all the fine crumbs, hair, lint ect, I have 7 grand babies, all very close in age, and when they eat…….oh my word, the crumbs, food, debris. You get it!! This broom conquers it all. Light weight it not cumbersome, easy to use my oldest grandchild, can help me sweep with ease! That’s a GOOD THING!! ☺️

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Rubber Bumper Breakes
reviews.reviewText: I have had two of this broom. I like the look and the way it works but in each case the rubber bumper breaks and comes off after less than a year. Then the broom bangs into things and you worry about banging up chair legs, doors, cabinetry etc. I feel this is a defect. I think a replacement bumber band should be supplied or available as a replacement part.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Should have bought a long time ago...
reviews.reviewText: Why did I keep using that old, messed up broom?! This one is really nice, works great, and ALWAYS looking for recycled or non-plastic products. This does both and good deal.

reviews.reviewTitle: Elegant, sturdy and beautifully made. Super happy.
reviews.reviewText: What an awesome product. Works great, is very sturdy and does its job. I have owned it for a few months now and it shows no sign of slowing down. Best part is when I am done with it, it will bio degrade. I hated my old plastic brooms that broke, and then were garbage. Will never go back!
